Abolished 1.4.1971 and added to the parish of Adderbury.
Abolished 1.4.1932 and added to the parish of Shutford.

On 30.9.1895 the part in Warwickshire was transferred to 
    Oxfordshire, so that thereafter Mollington was entirely in Oxfordshire.
Abolished 1.4.1932 and added to the parish of Banbury.

In 1889 the part of the parish of Warkworth in the municipal borough 
    of Banbury became part of Oxfordshire, in 1894 this area became part of the 
    parish of Grimsbury, so that thereafter Warkworth was again wholly in Northamptonshire. 
    See also Table 2, note (e).
Abolished 1.4.1971 and added to the parish of Adderbury.
